      {
        "id": 4059953,
        "name": "Brian G r a f s t r o m",
        "username": "Brian_G_r_a_f_s_t_r_o_m",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/brian_g_r_a_f_s_t_r_o_m/{size}/98878_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-04-26T00:16:32.650Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-Grand_Cru_Cru\" data-username=\"Arv_R\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"300198\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/arv_r/48/76949_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Arv_R:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I was just reading David peppercorn old book on Bordeaux and he thinks their blanc is better than their rouge.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>This is the only white of theirs I\u2019ve tried; it\u2019s unlikely I\u2019ll be trying another anytime soon.  Their red, on the other hand, is a wine I\u2019ve recently made into an annual \u201cgotta try at least one bottle\u201d wine; I quite liked the '15 and '16 here, although the '19 was less to my liking.</p>",
