        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/steve_costigan/{size}/273510_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-05-01T15:13:45.950Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Sounds grim and like a lot to unpack. Unfortunate because Bdx blanc can be among the most sublime white wines. The market for the consumer has too many expensive, and may I say overpriced, cuvees and scant pickings in the more affordable range. Yet there is an ocean of grapes in the region. Seems like Bdx blanc and its associated issues might be a great topic to expose for a talented wine writer <img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/images/emoji/unicode/wink.png?v=12\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":wink:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
